    {"start": "0x3680", "end": "0x4900", "kind": "data", "width": 16, "comment": "shared sprite atlas — column-major 4×N sprites. Sprite-start addresses below are derived from `LDA #lo;STA &1194; LDA #hi;STA &1195` patterns in CODE/CODE2/CODE3 plus the LEVD2 enemy-ptr-table entries that point into this region. Boundaries are approximate where the code references don't pin them down — refine as we learn more."},
    {"start": "0x493F", "end": "0x494F", "kind": "data", "width": 16, "comment": "palette_top — only [0..11] are read by the IRQ; [12..15] are present but unused. DEFAULT bytes are the scenario-1 palette (red/yellow). Scenarios 2-4 are loaded by Loader2 PROCL34 / PROCL56 / PROCL78 which `READ T%?&493F` 16 bytes each from DATA at lines 1160 / 1180 / 1200 (dispatched from L%=?&9D at lines 940-970)."},
    {"start": "0x494F", "end": "0x495F", "kind": "data", "width": 16, "comment": "palette_bottom — scoreboard zone, always black/blue/cyan/white. Same 12-effective-entries layout as palette_top."}
